Continuing education hours for credit may be compiled in the following areas:
Cassette and audiovisual presentations;
Professional seminars;
Accredited schools participating in continuing education programs;
Professional association-sponsored programs;
Correspondence courses;
Continuing education television series; or
Other programs as approved by the board.

Sponsors of continuing education programs shall submit a program schedule and outline to the board not less than thirty (30) days prior to the date of the program, including the following information:
The name of the course;
The name of the sponsoring organization;
The objectives of the program;
The number of hours over which the educational program will be presented and the dates presented;
The names of the instructors and speakers and their educational background and other relevant qualifications;
The location at which the program will be presented; and
The name and address of the person authorized to certify attendance at the program.

Board approval of continuing education programs shall be determined on the following basis:
If the program is likely to contribute to the advancement and extension of professional knowledge and skill in the practice of funeral service;
If the speakers, lecturers, and others participating in the program are recognized by the board as being qualified in the field;
If the program is available to all embalmers and funeral directors licensed in this state; and
If any fees charged for the program are the same for nonmembers of any organization sponsoring the program. Any difference in fees charged to nonmembers, as opposed to members of the sponsoring organization, shall be reasonably and directly related to the sponsoring organization's expense in operating the program.
